    "narrative": "For LawDog today, **Tyler Freeman** is our clear headliner with an efficiency score of 67.69. He draws a highly favorable matchup against the right-handed Randy V\u00e1squez (5.43 xERA), and assuming he retains his spot at the top of the lineup, he benefits from an 8% boost for his high-leverage order position. While the base projection for **Gleyber Torres** sits slightly lower at 51.30, he remains a solid start; he is facing the vulnerable Abel (4.28 xERA), and despite a negative platoon adjustment, his presence at the #2 spot anchors our offensive floor. **Gavin Sheets** and **Geraldo Perdomo** round out the active starters, though they are categorized as marginal plays. **Gavin Sheets** carries a 47.36 score, buoyed by a +7% platoon advantage, while **Geraldo Perdomo** faces a stiff challenge against Nolan McLean (3.04 xERA), making him a riskier start than his 41.97 score suggests.\n\nThe most difficult bench decision involved **Lawrence Butler**, who possessed the underlying metrics to compete for a spot but was ultimately excluded due to the unfavorable left-on-left dynamic against Ryan Weathers and current lineup status. With stars like **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez**, **Cal Raleigh**, and **Will Smith** inactive due to team off-days, our bench depth is intentionally thin to preserve game caps for later in the week. We are keeping a close watch on the official lineups for **Gavin Sheets**, **Geraldo Perdomo**, and **Tyler Freeman**; as these are currently \"Lineup Pending,\" any slide down the batting order would immediately compress their efficiency scores and potentially trigger a re-evaluation of their utility against our remaining assets like **Bryson Stott**, **Daulton Varsho**, **Taylor Ward**, **Yainer Diaz**, **Jonathan Aranda**, **Matt Chapman**, **Wenceel Perez**, **Luis Arraez**, **Masyn Winn**, **Brendan Donovan**, **Jung Hoo Lee**, **Jeremiah Jackson**, or **Drew Gilbert**.",
